-- Northwest Natural Gas earnings rise on gain
-- 
-- Fri Jul 25, 2008 8:08am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/25/us-northwest-idUSBNG27134620080725

 

 (Reuters) - Natural-gas distributor Northwest Natural Gas Co ( NWN.N ) reported a 26 percent rise in quarterly profit, mainly on a gain from the sale of an airplane. 

 For the second quarter, the company reported net income of $3.3 million, or 12 cents a share, compared with $2.6 million, or 10 cents a share, a year ago. The results included a gain of $1.1 million on the sale of a Boeing 737 airplane, which the company had purchased and leased to Continental Airlines. Gross operating revenue of the company, which distributes natural gas in Oregon and southwest Washington, grew 4 percent to $191.3 million. Excluding exceptional items, the company's profit was 8 cents a share, below analysts' expectation of 11 cents a share, according to Reuters Estimates. Analysts were expecting revenue of $202.7 million. Northwest reaffirmed its 2008 earnings outlook of $2.48 to $2.63 a share. Analysts are expecting earnings of $2.59 a share, excluding special items, for the period. Shares of the Portland, Oregon-based company closed at $45.94 Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange. (Reporting by Shradhha Sharma in Bangalore; Editing by Vinu Pilakkott)